  "ftir_info": "Not reported in the article.",
  "tablet_fabrications": {
    "general_procedure": "Tablets compressed using single punch carver hydraulic hand press (model c, Carver Inc., USA) with 10.5 mm diameter die at four pressures: 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 1.25 MN/m². Die and punch lubricated with 1% w/v magnesium stearate in acetone.",
    "batch_specific_data": "For factorial batches 1-8, tensile strength (KgF), friability (%), and disintegration time (min) are reported in Table 1 (see formulation_details_batches). Other properties (thickness, weight variation, crushing strength, drug content, density, consolidation index) not reported per factorial batch. See Tables 3 and 4 for properties of individual polymer formulations (NG, PMG, CMG, HPMC at 4% and 8% by direct compression and wet granulation) – examples below.",
